on/state update and recommendation scoring. Unit tests of ranking logic alone miss propagation or stale-state failures.","test_description":"Execute integration flow: request recommendations, mark one recommended item as purchased, issue a second request for same user, and assert purchased item rank drops (or is removed per policy).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":10,"description":"Recommendations are deterministic for identical user state with no intervening activity.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Determinism can fail due to cross-module effects (unstable sort keys, nondeterministic iteration, cache/state mutation). A single-function unit test may miss pipeline-level nondeterminism.","test_description":"Run the full in-process recommendation pipeline twice with identical user snapshot, catalog snapshot, and seeds/config; assert exact ranked-list equality across calls.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
